        <h3 id = "stock-holders" class = "theme1">
            Stock Holders
        </h3>
        <p class = "theme2">
            Stock holders use a xy graph to check the increase or decrease of a certain stock, and to determine if they should sell the stock.
        </p>
        <h3 id = "teachers" class = "theme1">
            Teachers
        </h3>
        <p class = "theme2">
            Teachers use a double bar graph to see how much the children have improved in a test.
        </p>
        <h3 id = "survey-companies" class = "theme1">
            Survey Companies
        </h3>
        <p class = "theme2">
            Survey company workers just need a glance, and can know all the results of a survey.
        </p>
        <h2 class = "theme1">
            How can we use graphs?
        </h2>
        <h5 class = "theme1">
            Seriously. After this long and boring lesson of graphs, how do we even use them in our daily life? If we can't use them, then why are we using them?
        </h5>
        <ul class = "theme2">
            <li>Using a bar graph, we want to know what things are the most popular when we have a school fair</li>
            <li>Using a double bar graph, on the other hand, can give out two attributes of one thing, like a pretest and a posttest between different people.</li>
            <li>Using a line graph, we can see our time efficiency on homework on a daily basis</li>
            <li>Using a circle graph, we can see our time or amount of each type of homework</li>
        </ul>
        <h1 class = "theme1">
            Types of Graphs
        </h1>
        <h2 id = "bar-graph" class = "theme1">
            Bar Graph
        </h2>
        <img class = "tog-pic" alt = "favorite fruit bar graph" src = "http://www.velaction.com/lean-information/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/bar-chart-vertical-300x180.jpg">
        <p class = "theme2">
            A bar graph is, as its name suggests, a graph that has bars to represent the item. The y line is the amount of that item, and the x line is that item. A bar graph is normally used to see which item is the most popular/ favorite.
        </p>
        <p><br></p>
        <h2 id = "circle-graph" class = "theme1">
            Circle Graph
        </h2>
        <img class = "tog-pic" alt = "favorite fruit circle graph" src = "http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-33IaJQjNINc/Uxe1K-ianKI/AAAAAAAAAcg/PhANd-W3gpc/s1600/Screenshot+from+2014-03-06+12:33:59.png">
        <p class = "theme2">
            A circle graph is like a pie, so its other name is a pie chart. The uses of a circle graph is like a bar graph. The size of a slice is the amount of that item (in percentages).
        </p>
        <p><br></p>
        <h2 id = "double-bar-graph" class = "theme1">
            Double Bar Graph
        </h2>
        <img class = "tog-pic" alt = "practice test and test scores double bar graph" src = "http://cdn-3.ask-math.com/images/Doublebargraph.png">
        <p class = "theme2">
            A double bar graph is a graph which every item has 2 entries. They could be the difference of scores in a practice test and the real test.
        </p>
        <p><br></p>
        <!--HSBC-->
        <h2 id = "line-graph" class = "theme1">
            Line Graph
        </h2>
        <img class = "tog-pic" alt = "5 day price of HSBC stock price line graph" src = "https://encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQp2oA4itmp4kDEBvgjzLOPrZGIrXk65eUiJhG9pgLaf517T6sQlg">
        <p class = "theme2">
            A line graph is perfect for ongoing things, like stocks because they are constantly moving.
        </p>
        <p><br></p>
